    public static final String Rom_2_29 = "But he [is] a Jew, which is one inwardly; and circumcision [is that] of the heart, in the spirit, [and] not in the letter; whose praise [is] not of men, but of God. ";
    public static final String Rom_3_1 = "What advantage then hath the Jew? or what profit [is there] of circumcision? ";
    public static final String Rom_3_2 = "Much every way: chiefly, because that unto them were committed the oracles of God. ";
    public static final String Rom_3_3 = "For what if some did not believe? shall their unbelief make the faith of God without effect? ";
    public static final String Rom_3_4 = "God forbid: yea, let God be true, but every man a liar; as it is written, That thou mightest be justified in thy sayings, and mightest overcome when thou art judged. ";
    public static final String Rom_3_5 = "But if our unrighteousness commend the righteousness of God, what shall we say? [Is] God unrighteous who taketh vengeance? (I speak as a man) ";
    public static final String Rom_3_6 = "God forbid: for then how shall God judge the world? ";
    public static final String Rom_3_7 = "For if the truth of God hath more abounded through my lie unto his glory; why yet am I also judged as a sinner? ";
    public static final String Rom_3_8 = "And not [rather,] (as we be slanderously reported, and as some affirm that we say,) Let us do evil, that good may come? whose damnation is just. ";
    public static final String Rom_3_9 = "What then? are we better [than they?] No, in no wise: for we have before proved both Jews and Gentiles, that they are all under sin; ";
    public static final String Rom_3_10 = "As it is written, There is none righteous, no, not one: ";
