    public static final String Rom_7_24 = "O wretched man that I am! who shall deliver me from the body of this death? ";
    public static final String Rom_7_25 = "I thank God through Jesus Christ our Lord. So then with the mind I myself serve the law of God; but with the flesh the law of sin. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_1 = "[There is] therefore now no condemnation to them which are in Christ Jesus, who walk not after the flesh, but after the Spirit. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_2 = "For the law of the Spirit of life in Christ Jesus hath made me free from the law of sin and death. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_3 = "For what the law could not do, in that it was weak through the flesh, God sending his own Son in the likeness of sinful flesh, and for sin, condemned sin in the flesh: ";
    public static final String Rom_8_4 = "That the righteousness of the law might be fulfilled in us, who walk not after the flesh, but after the Spirit. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_5 = "For they that are after the flesh do mind the things of the flesh; but they that are after the Spirit the things of the Spirit. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_6 = "For to be carnally minded [is] death; but to be spiritually minded [is] life and peace. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_7 = "Because the carnal mind [is] enmity against God: for it is not subject to the law of God, neither indeed can be. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_8 = "So then they that are in the flesh cannot please God. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_9 = "But ye are not in the flesh, but in the Spirit, if so be that the Spirit of God dwell in you. Now if any man have not the Spirit of Christ, he is none of his. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_10 = "And if Christ [be] in you, the body [is] dead because of sin; but the Spirit [is] life because of righteousness. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_11 = "But if the Spirit of him that raised up Jesus from the dead dwell in you, he that raised up Christ from the dead shall also quicken your mortal bodies by his Spirit that dwelleth in you. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_12 = "Therefore, brethren, we are debtors, not to the flesh, to live after the flesh. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_13 = "For if ye live after the flesh, ye shall die: but if ye through the Spirit do mortify the deeds of the body, ye shall live. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_14 = "For as many as are led by the Spirit of God, they are the sons of God. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_15 = "For ye have not received the spirit of bondage again to fear; but ye have received the Spirit of adoption, whereby we cry, Abba, Father. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_16 = "The Spirit itself beareth witness with our spirit, that we are the children of God: ";
    public static final String Rom_8_17 = "And if children, then heirs; heirs of God, and joint-heirs with Christ; if so be that we suffer with [him,] that we may be also glorified together. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_18 = "For I reckon that the sufferings of this present time [are] not worthy [to be compared] with the glory which shall be revealed in us. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_19 = "For the earnest expectation of the creature waiteth for the manifestation of the sons of God. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_20 = "For the creature was made subject to vanity, not willingly, but by reason of him who hath subjected [the same] in hope, ";
    public static final String Rom_8_21 = "Because the creature itself also shall be delivered from the bondage of corruption into the glorious liberty of the children of God. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_22 = "For we know that the whole creation groaneth and travaileth in pain together until now. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_23 = "And not only [they,] but ourselves also, which have the firstfruits of the Spirit, even we ourselves groan within ourselves, waiting for the adoption, [to wit,] the redemption of our body. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_24 = "For we are saved by hope: but hope that is seen is not hope: for what a man seeth, why doth he yet hope for? ";
    public static final String Rom_8_25 = "But if we hope for that we see not, [then] do we with patience wait for [it. ]";
    public static final String Rom_8_26 = "Likewise the Spirit also helpeth our infirmities: for we know not what we should pray for as we ought: but the Spirit itself maketh intercession for us with groanings which cannot be uttered. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_27 = "And he that searcheth the hearts knoweth what [is] the mind of the Spirit, because he maketh intercession for the saints according to [the will of] God. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_28 = "And we know that all things work together for good to them that love God, to them who are the called according to [his] purpose. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_29 = "For whom he did foreknow, he also did predestinate [to be] conformed to the image of his Son, that he might be the firstborn among many brethren. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_30 = "Moreover whom he did predestinate, them he also called: and whom he called, them he also justified: and whom he justified, them he also glorified. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_31 = "What shall we then say to these things? If God [be] for us, who [can be] against us? ";
    public static final String Rom_8_32 = "He that spared not his own Son, but delivered him up for us all, how shall he not with him also freely give us all things? ";
    public static final String Rom_8_33 = "Who shall lay any thing to the charge of God's elect? [It is] God that justifieth. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_34 = "Who [is] he that condemneth? [It is] Christ that died, yea rather, that is risen again, who is even at the right hand of God, who also maketh intercession for us. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_35 = "Who shall separate us from the love of Christ? [shall] tribulation, or distress, or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or peril, or sword? ";
    public static final String Rom_8_36 = "As it is written, For thy sake we are killed all the day long; we are accounted as sheep for the slaughter. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_37 = "Nay, in all these things we are more than conquerors through him that loved us. ";
    public static final String Rom_8_38 = "For I am persuaded, that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor principalities, nor powers, nor things present, nor things to come, ";
    public static final String Rom_8_39 = "Nor height, nor depth, nor any other creature, shall be able to separate us from the love of God, which is in Christ Jesus our Lord. ";
    public static final String Rom_9_1 = "I say the truth in Christ, I lie not, my conscience also bearing me witness in the Holy Ghost, ";
    public static final String Rom_9_2 = "That I have great heaviness and continual sorrow in my heart. ";
    public static final String Rom_9_3 = "For I could wish that myself were accursed from Christ for my brethren, my kinsmen according to the flesh: ";
