    public static final String Rom_11_21 = "For if God spared not the natural branches, [take heed] lest he also spare not thee. ";
    public static final String Rom_11_22 = "Behold therefore the goodness and severity of God: on them which fell, severity; but toward thee, goodness, if thou continue in [his] goodness: otherwise thou also shalt be cut off. ";
    public static final String Rom_11_23 = "And they also, if they abide not still in unbelief, shall be graffed in: for God is able to graff them in again. ";
    public static final String Rom_11_24 = "For if thou wert cut out of the olive tree which is wild by nature, and wert graffed contrary to nature into a good olive tree: how much more shall these, which be the natural [branches,] be graffed into their own olive tree? ";
    public static final String Rom_11_25 = "For I would not, brethren, that ye should be ignorant of this mystery, lest ye should be wise in your own conceits; that blindness in part is happened to Israel, until the fulness of the Gentiles be come in. ";
    public static final String Rom_11_26 = "And so all Israel shall be saved: as it is written, There shall come out of Sion the Deliverer, and shall turn away ungodliness from Jacob: ";
    public static final String Rom_11_27 = "For this [is] my covenant unto them, when I shall take away their sins. ";
    public static final String Rom_11_28 = "As concerning the gospel, [they are] enemies for your sakes: but as touching the election, [they are] beloved for the fathers' sakes. ";
